<div class="blogbody">

<h3 class="title">California Pizza Kitchen Execs Hear IMC Presentations</h3>

<table width='100%' border='0'>
	<tr>
	<td><p><span class='featuresubhead'><!--begin subhead--><!--end subhead--></span></p><p>Story by mns</p>

<p><TABLE width=150 align=right border=0 HSPACE="10"><br />
<TBODY><br />
<TR><br />
<TD><IMG height=201 src="http://www.medill.northwestern.edu/medill/inside/cpk-cesar-150x201.jpg" width=150 vspace=5 border=0> <FONT face="Arial, Helvetica" size=3><I>Cesar Lopez, the "CEO" of one of the presentation groups, makes a point.</I></FONT> </TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE><br />
<TABLE width=103 align=right border=0 HSPACE="10"><br />
<TBODY><br />
<TR><br />
<TD><A href="http://www.cpk.com/"><FONT face="Times New Roman"><IMG height=83 src="http://www.medill.northwestern.edu/medill/inside/cpk-logo-103x83.gif" width=103 vspace=5 border=0></FONT></A> </TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE><br />
<P>Three top corporate executives, the Chicago regional manager and five area store managers from <A href="http://www.cpk.com/">California Pizza Kitchen</A> came to Medill on Wednesday to hear relationship marketing presentations from five groups of graduate integrated marketing communications (IMC) students. <br />
<P>On hand to hear the results of Winter Quarter projects by associate professor Paul Wang's "Database Management &amp; Application" class were Fred Hipp, CPK president; Fred Wolfe, senior vice president of operations; Sarah Goldsmith, vice president of marketing; Fred Morgan, regional manager; and the managers of stores in Oak Brook, Schaumburg, Skokie's Old Orchard Mall, and Water Tower Place and River North in downtown Chicago. <br />
<P>"We're listening to a large part of our core audience telling us from an academic and strategic standpoint how to improve our business -- what we're doing right, and what we're doing wrong," Hipp said. This is the third year the Los Angeles-based company has visited Medill, and "we're talking about enhancing our participation," he said. <br />
<TABLE width=180 align=left border=0 HSPACE="10"><br />
<TBODY><br />
<TR><br />
<TD><IMG height=161 src="http://www.medill.northwestern.edu/medill/inside/cpk-hipp-180x161.jpg" width=180 vspace=5 border=0> <FONT face="Arial, Helvetica" size=3><I>Fred Hipp, president of California Pizza Kitchen, had a battery of questions for students.</I></FONT> </TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE><br />
<P>Morgan said he came to "learn more about our customers and figure out ways to increase sales and become more profitable by getting some new ideas for marketing." Each CPK store has its own special needs, he added. <br />
<P>One presentation led by "CEO" Cesar Lopez, a student from Colombia, saw strengths in CPK's image as a healthy, innovative company that presents a "slice of California." The group saw room to improve CPK's name recognition outside California and clarify the company's image. Customer interviews and surveys, which students conducted along with quantitative research, found people pictured the restaurant chain's typical customer as ranging from Elton John, to Dennis Rodman, to an old man. <br />
<P>The internationally flavored student group -- which included Supreeya Kanikananta of Thailand, Kunal Khattar and Babu Monie of India, and Americans Sheena Steiner and Brad Bentley -- recommended the tag-line, "Naturally Good." <br />
<P>Hipp came armed with a flurry of questions about everything from how targeted increases in customer base were calculated, to how to point out low-fat items without making the rest of the menu seem suspect. <BR><br />
<TABLE width=355 align=center border=0 HSPACE="10"><br />
<TBODY><br />
<TR><br />
<TD width=130><IMG height=137 src="http://www.medill.northwestern.edu/medill/inside/cpk-morgan-130x137.jpg" width=130 vspace=5 border=0> </TD><br />
<TD align=TOP width=225><IMG height=137 src="http://www.medill.northwestern.edu/medill/inside/cpk-group-225x137.jpg" width=225 vspace=5 border=0> </TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE><br />
<TABLE width=355 align=center border=0 HSPACE="10"><br />
<TBODY><br />
<TR><br />
<TD width=130><FONT face="Arial, Helvetica" size=3><I>Regional manager Fred Morgan brought managers from all five Chicago-area CPK stores: Old Orchard, River North, Water Tower, Oak Brook and Schaumburg.</I></FONT> </TD><br />
<TD align=TOP width=225><FONT face="Arial, Helvetica" size=3><I>Joining professor Paul Wang (right) were (from left) Fred Wolfe, senior vice president of operations; Sarah Goldsmith, vice president of marketing; and Fred Hipp, president.</I></FONT> </TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></P></td></tr></table></p>

<a name="more"></a>

<br /><br />
<span class="posted">Posted March 12, 1999 02:56 PM
<br /><br />

